      <hedline>
        <hl1>Gay Marriage And the Campaign</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Barbara Bonn letter agrees with Gary Bauer (Oct 8 Op-Ed) about evasions exhibited by both Gov Bush and Dick Cheney on issues of abortion and gay marriage</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Fuzzy Morality,'' by Gary Bauer (Op-Ed, Oct. 8):</p>
        <p>I never expected to agree with Gary Bauer about anything in this lifetime, but he is absolutely right about the evasions exhibited in the recent debates by both George W. Bush and Dick Cheney on the issues of abortion and gay marriage.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Fuzzy Morality,'' by Gary Bauer (Op-Ed, Oct. 8):</p>
        <p>I never expected to agree with Gary Bauer about anything in this lifetime, but he is absolutely right about the evasions exhibited in the recent debates by both George W. Bush and Dick Cheney on the issues of abortion and gay marriage.</p>
        <p>While I disagree totally with the Republican platform on these issues, I would expect the party's standard bearers to present its views honestly. Instead, both candidates dodged and fudged, thereby signaling the public that trolling for votes is  more important to them than supporting the principles they upheld so courageously in the partisan safety of their own convention.</p>
        <p>BARBARA BONN  New York, Oct. 8, 2000</p>
      </block>
